      <p>A month in Sri Lanka is a genuine privilege — enough time to slow down, go deep, and discover corners of the island that the week-long itineraries never reach. You can cover the full coastal circuit, spend real time in the north (which most visitors skip entirely), include multiple wildlife safaris, do a proper multi-day trek in the Knuckles, and still have days to simply sit in a guesthouse garden in Ella and read. This itinerary is designed for December–April (when both coasts are accessible).</p>

